description:
Application was designed for CommCareODK 2.0 and was deployed on smartphones in Hindi language.  The app consists of 7 modules- 5 related to child nutrition and health, and 2 related to pregnancy. All child modules share the same case type but have module filtering so the case lists only show the relevant cases.  There are four case types- child, mother, child referral, and mother referral.

The first module contains screening and weight/height update forms for children.  The screening form requests lots of one-time data while updates can be made through the monthly weighing form.  A unique ID is generated for each child.

The second and third modules have forms for following up with MAM and SAM children, respectively.  Both modules also have vaccination forms which have complex logic to display the relevant vaccinations at the appropriate age, and that "remembers" whether the CHW answered yes to a vaccination at the last visit, so it is not asked again.

One module contains follow up questions specific to children six months and under.

Another module contains a set of forms intended for pregnant women, including registration/screening, follow up, and birth details.  Registering a birth automatically opens a child case.

The two final modules are referral forms for children and pregnant women, respectively.  These are separate cases that can be opened from most of the follow up or screening forms, and are intended to help the CHW prioritize cases that needed extra attention.

This application is undergoing frequent revision/updating, and feedback would be greatly appreciated by the SNEHA team.
